Phase 1: Extracting domain model...
  Saved: /Users/ignatdubovskiy/WebstormProjects/idf/refs/extracted/2026-04-19-indeed-jobs-mobile.json

Phase 2: Generating candidate pattern...

  Already covered:
    Two-field search (What + Where) occupies nearly half the home screen — dominant primary input surface → inline-search
    Job card is minimalist: title, company+location line, highlighted salary, 3-4 description bullets, single primary Apply CTA plus Save/Share icons → grid-card-layout
    App-install interstitial on web is a documented anti-pattern forcing mobile-app adoption → anti-pattern
    AI relevance filter silently removes up to 90% of matches with no user control — opaque algorithmic gate → anti-pattern
    No ghost-job reporting mechanism — stale listings persist without user-driven expiry signal → anti-pattern
    Resume is a single unified document auto-attached to every Quick Apply — no per-application customization surface → anti-pattern
    Application tracker is visually thin: 'viewed' status and silence are the dominant states — weak post-apply feedback loop → anti-pattern

